  "intent": "For this DNA post-PCR cleanup protocol, you'll be working with the reservoir in slot 5, plate2 at room temperature, and the magnetic plate, so first make sure to refill the 300 \u00b5L tip box and empty the tip waste before we begin. Start by disengaging the magnets to release the beads, then mix 10 times with 64 \u00b5L in column 0 and let it incubate for 10 minutes before engaging the magnets at the specified height for bead separation. After the magnetic separation pause, transfer 60 \u00b5L from source to destination with the programmed wait times (1 second, then 30 seconds), then disengage magnets again and transfer 22 \u00b5L from the multiple source wells to destination wells, incubating for 2 minutes before re-engaging magnets. Finally, place a fresh 200 \u00b5L PCR plate on the temperature module and transfer 20 \u00b5L from source A1 to destination A1 to complete the post-PCR cleanup steps.",
